# JavaScript – String Methods

---

## 📘 String Basics

```js
const str = "Hello, World!";

str.length          // 13
str[0]              // "H"
str.at(-1)          // "!" (last char, ES2022)
typeof str          // "string"

// Strings are immutable — methods return NEW strings
```

---

## 🔍 Searching & Checking

```js
const str = "Hello, World!";

// Find position
str.indexOf("o")         // 4  (first occurrence, -1 if not found)
str.lastIndexOf("o")     // 8
str.search(/world/i)     // 7  (regex search, returns index)

// Check existence
str.includes("World")    // true
str.startsWith("Hello")  // true
str.endsWith("!")        // true
str.startsWith("World", 7) // true (start from index 7)
```

---

## ✂️ Extracting

```js
const str = "Hello, World!";

// slice(start, end) — end is exclusive, supports negative
str.slice(7, 12)     // "World"
str.slice(-6)        // "World!"
str.slice(7)         // "World!"

// substring(start, end) — no negatives
str.substring(7, 12) // "World"

// charAt
str.charAt(0)        // "H"
```

---

## 🔄 Transforming

```js
const str = "  Hello, World!  ";

// Case
str.toUpperCase()        // "  HELLO, WORLD!  "
str.toLowerCase()        // "  hello, world!  "

// Trim whitespace
str.trim()               // "Hello, World!"
str.trimStart()          // "Hello, World!  "
str.trimEnd()            // "  Hello, World!"

// Replace
"hello world".replace("world", "JS")       // "hello JS" (first only)
"aabbcc".replaceAll("b", "x")              // "aaxxcc"
"hello".replace(/l/g, "r")                 // "herro" (regex global)

// Repeat & Pad
"ha".repeat(3)            // "hahaha"
"5".padStart(3, "0")      // "005"
"5".padEnd(3, "0")        // "500"
```

